## Rollback Plan

### If Issues Occur

1. **Portal:** Redeploy previous version (remapping methods will fail but won't break existing functionality)
2. **Service:** Redeploy previous version (will use original query without remapping)
3. **Database:** Keep table (data preserved for re-deployment), or drop table if needed

**Data Loss Risk:** None (base tables unchanged, remapping table is additive)

## Benefits

1. **Non-Invasive:** No changes to existing tables
2. **Zero Migration:** No data migration required
3. **Backward Compatible:** Parts without remapping use original order automatically
4. **Simple Logic:** Base configuration + optional transformation
5. **Storage Efficient:** Only stores differences
6. **Flexible:** Support any area/side combination
7. **Performance:** Single LEFT JOIN query
8. **Maintainable:** Update remapping without touching base config

## Comparison: Remapping vs Full Duplication

| Aspect | Remapping Approach ✅ | Full Duplication ❌ |
|--------|---------------------|-------------------|
| Migration | None required | All records need AreaID/Side |
| Storage | Only differences | Full config per area/side |
| Code Changes | Minimal (LEFT JOIN) | Extensive (all CRUD) |
| Deployment Risk | Low (new table) | High (schema changes) |
| Rollback | Easy (drop table) | Difficult (restore backup) |
| Understanding | Intuitive (1→3 mapping) | Complex (fallback logic) |
| Performance | Single LEFT JOIN | CTE with UNIONs |
| Maintenance | Update remapping only | Update multiple configs |

